issue.title: More whiteboard words

repository.name: bugbug
repository.description: Platform for Machine Learning projects on Software Engineering

issue.body:
Fixes #104.

Based on these changes, if whiteboard consists of `[memshrink:XX][qf:p3]`, the function converts them into `memshrink` and `qf`. (Only words containing `:` are extracted for this purpose).

body: @marco-c, @ayush1999  I would like to work on this issue could you help me with initial steps

The test data in the `test/fixtures/bug_features` directory is really messy. We'd like to remove all redundant keys from each test element in all test files and keep only the element being tested. So each line in `has_str.json` will be a dict containing only `has_str` key, for example.

i would like to work on this issue.
Can you guide me @ayush1999
The process is pretty much summed up in my earlier comment (https://github.com/mozilla/bugbug/issues/126#issuecomment-459639958). Please tell me if you need help understanding any aspect of it.

@ayush1999  Can you please explain a little more about what "each line in has_str.json will be a dict containing has_str only.
I get that we are removing the redundant fields in the dict but it's my first time with this data so can you help me walkthrough this data. 
I'd appreciate  the help.
Thankyou.

@HSR05 Each line is the test file is a dict, suppose `{'a': val1, 'b':val2, 'c':val3}` and so on. If the test file is for the `a` field, we can remove the other fields (`b` and `c`), so that the line becomes `{'a':val1}` only, since the other fields aren't of any use to us.
Got it. I'll work on it. Thanks for the guidance ðŸ‘ @ayush1999

@ayush1999 

> each test element in `has_str.json` had only the `has_str` key.

Can you please clarify once again because the has_str.json file does not have any has_str key. 
Same goes for the other files like has_urls.json. I cannot find any key has_urls.
If there is anything wrong with my udnerstanding can you please clarify the issue once again?
Thankyou.

`has_str` is just a bug extractor. It doesn't search for the `has_str` key. For the key, see : https://github.com/mozilla/bugbug/blob/master/bugbug/bug_features.py#L27 (and similar for other bug extractors)
Can I work on this issue?
@parthpm I am already working on it, if i find any difficulty i'll update this thread and you can help along. Cheers ðŸ‘
